com.energyxxer.commodore.functionlogic.coordinates

Class CoordinateSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.energyxxer.commodore.functionlogic.coordinates.CoordinateSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ExecuteModifier

    public class CoordinateSet
extends java.lang.Object
implements ExecuteModifier
    Represents a set of three coordinates, for axes x, y and z.
    This doubles as an execute modifier class for the execute positioned <x> <y> <z> subcommand.
    See Also:
    Coordinate, ExecuteModifier

      • getXZAs

        public java.lang.String getXZAs(@NotNull
                                Coordinate.DisplayMode mode)
        Turns this coordinate set into a string that can be used in a command, using the specified display mode.
        Unlike the getAs(com.energyxxer.commodore.functionlogic.coordinates.Coordinate.DisplayMode) method, this method only prints out the x and z coordinates for commands that use strictly two-dimensional coordinates, disregarding altitude.
        Parameters:
        mode - The mode this coordinate set should be printed as.
        Returns:
        The string representing this coordinate set's X and Z coordinates.
